Preheat your grill to high. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni.

Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Halfway through, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%g} to the pan and stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken and bacon to a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high and melt in the @Butter{30%g}.

Once melted, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @Flour{30%g}.

Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @Water for the Sauce{250%ml} a little at a time, followed by the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and both cheeses. @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} and @Tenderstem Broccoli{150%g}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Stir the pasta, chicken and bacon into the sauce. Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then transfer to a #baking dish{}.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Grill your pasta bake until golden and crispy, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into the (now empty) saucepan with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Bring back to the boil, then add the broccoli and cook until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a colander, then return to the saucepan. Drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @?pepper{} if you'd like.

When everything is ready, plate up your ultimate chicken and bacon rigatoni bake with the broccoli alongside. Enjoy!